e-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-scholars-ulema","tag-anger-al-ghadab","tag-enjoining-good","tag-gentleness-al-rifq","tag-hearing-al-sama","tag-humility-al-tawadu","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-manners-adab","tag-revenge-al-intiqam"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-8KJ","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":26911,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/12\/13\/ibn-masud-enjoining-gentle\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":0},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Enjoining: He would not be mad at them, he was gentle","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 13, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ahmad ibn Hanbal reported: The companions of Ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, if they passed by people from whom they saw something they disapproved, they would say, \u201cTake it easy, may Allah have mercy on you.\u201d Source: al-Amr bil-Ma\u02bbru\u0304f lil-Khalla\u0304l 1\/25 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u062d\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064d \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26908,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/12\/13\/enjoin-good-gentle-fair-knowledge\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":1},"title":"Sufyan on Enjoining: Forbid evil with gentleness, justice, knowledge","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 13, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Khallal reported: Sufyan al-Thawri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThere is no enjoining good or forbidding evil except for one who has three qualities: gentleness in what he enjoins and forbids, justice in what he enjoins and forbids, and knowledge of what he enjoins and forbids.\u201d Source: al-Amr\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33627,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/25\/ibn-abbas-confront-rulers\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Rulers: Do not confront rulers if they will kill you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 25, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019id ibn Jubayr reported: I asked Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, \u201cShall I enjoin good and forbid evil upon the ruler?\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cIf you fear he will kill you, then no.\u201d Then, I asked him again and he said the same to me. Then, I\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35529,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/04\/dua-amr-bil-maruf\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Supplication not answered unless enjoining good","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 4, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cEnjoin good and forbid evil before you call upon Allah and He does not answer you.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 4004 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14351,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/20\/enjoin-maruf-or-else\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Justice: Enjoin good and forbid evil, or else","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBy the One in whose hand is my soul, you must enjoin good and forbid evil, or else Allah will soon send punishment upon you. Then, you will call upon Allah and it will not be answered\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18477,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/10\/allah-will-abandon-them\/","url_meta":{"origin":33649,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Injustice: Muslims abandoned if fail to stop oppression","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 10, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen you see my